Reference-contexts: However, unstructured meshes present the more difficult task of grasping spatial relationships of unstructed 3D objects in 2-space. Mesh visualization is important for assessing solution accuracy, geometrical integrity (identifyingmissing and/or distorted elements), and interactive editing. One common technique to assist in viewing these meshes is to use clipping planes <ref> [2] </ref>. However, when applied to unstructured meshes, a clipping plane cuts through portions of elements, leaving line segments on the edges of the mesh. Speray and Kennon addressed this problem by devising a method of volume probes for interactive data exploration [4].
